=head1 DESCRIPTION

Lists the Amazon Web Services Private CA SCEP connectors belonging to
your Amazon Web Services account.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Arn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the connector.


=head2 CertificateAuthorityArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the connector's associated
certificate authority.


=head2 CreatedAt => Str

The date and time that the challenge was created.


=head2 Endpoint => Str

The connector's HTTPS public SCEP URL.


=head2 MobileDeviceManagement => L<Paws::PcaConnectorScep::MobileDeviceManagement>

Contains settings relevant to the mobile device management system that
you chose for the connector. If you didn't configure
C<MobileDeviceManagement>, then the connector is for general-purpose
use and this object is empty.


=head2 OpenIdConfiguration => L<Paws::PcaConnectorScep::OpenIdConfiguration>

Contains OpenID Connect (OIDC) parameters for use with Microsoft
Intune.


=head2 Status => Str

The connector's status. Status can be creating, active, deleting, or
failed.


=head2 StatusReason => Str

Information about why connector creation failed, if status is
C<FAILED>.


=head2 Type => Str

The connector type.


=head2 UpdatedAt => Str

The date and time that the challenge was updated.



